  "prompt": "What are the legal ramifications of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with significant legal consequences. Generally, these can include:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial fines\n- Imprisonment (often several years)\n- Federal and state level prosecution\n- Potential asset seizure\n\n2. Civil Consequences\n- Forfeiture of assets\n- Additional monetary penalties\n- Potential civil litigation\n\n3. Professional Implications\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Business disqualification\n- Damage to professional reputation\n\n4. International Consequences\n- Potential extradition\n- International financial sanctions\n- Travel restrictions\n\nSpecific penalties vary based on jurisdiction, amount involved, and specific circumstances. Consulting legal professionals is recommended for precise details.",
